# Modern UI rules

- Use a colourful, fun, modern aesthetic: clean but stylish.
- Pick strong colours that work well together, using recognised palettes 
- Prefer generous spacing, strong typography hierarchy, and rounded surfaces.
- Use subtle gradients, soft shadows, and restrained motion.
- Avoid generic default styling, crowded layouts, and overly saturated colors.
- Always make pages responsive and accessible.
- Prefer reusable components and consistent design tokens.
- Use native CSS (especially Flexbox and Grid) classes for all styling.
- Add polished empty states, loading states, and hover states.
- Keep sections visually distinct with spacing and contrast.
- Use emojis: musical, artistic, events, fun, etc. 